</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="S." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="S. notorrhoa" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">S. notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar externally. Reliable determination can be achieved by genitalia examination (DNA barcodes not available for all these three taxa yet). Uncus pentagonal, heavily sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris dividua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; rectangular, small, less sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris medullata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medullata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris medullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; oval and heavily sclerotised in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris notorrhoa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvae narrow basally, inner margin without sclerotisations in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nupponen 1 &amp; Sihvonen" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris dividua" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividua">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris dividua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; broad basally, inner margin with minute sclerotisation in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1916" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris medullata" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medullata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris medullata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; asymmetrical, inner margin with large sclerotisations in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", genus combination" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Meyrick" baseAuthorityYear="1921" class="Insecta" family="Scythrididae" genus="Scythris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Scythris notorrhoa" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notorrhoa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="19">Scythris notorrhoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Segment VIII distinct in each three species, see illustrations.
</paragraph>
